<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98417200446735></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98417200446735><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1590&mid=98417200446735>level and more info...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1590&mid=98417200446735#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1103><span id=Scholar>kazooie</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>88 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 9th 4:06 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can begin using the proc at lvl 45. Some more info on the gloves.. The casting time is 2 seconds longer than normal snare, and its the lvl 1 snare, NOT the lvl 29 wayyy improved ENsnare.&nbsp;&nbsp;it is very helpful if you want to free up an extra spell slot, but mana consumption is a laugh anyway at the snare line series.  15 mana for snare and i think its 25 for ensnare.  Doesn't really matter if we right click the gloves to save mana.  We can regain it by the time the spell effect goes off.  These are handy in a number of situations however.  Obviously one would be when you are low on mana, root, then snare the mob for a time to med in case root breaks.  Power levelling is also good for these if you dont wanna waste cast after cast on multiple mobs *shrug*  Also when you get really bored and feel like terrorizing an old easy zone like unrest of even some hill giants in the karanas, these kind of come in handy.  Because of the long casting time on them you must be careful to give yourself some extra range when the mob is running at you. (same with the arms).  I almost never would use these in dungeons either.  That extra 2 seconds adds up when you need the mana to heal/buff/what have you, and like i said the regular ensnare spell itself hardly takes any mana.  Hope that info helped. It's kind of a neat novelty item, and the green hands thing does seem to work well with the elfies ;-)<br>&nbsp;<br>Kazooie Swiftfoot<br>Druid of Solusek Ro</td></tr>
